After returning from the battlefield and several months
passing, Lloyd began to gradually understand and accept the
reality surrounding him. This change was also brought about
by the devoted actions of Amina.

Splitting firewood, hunting, helping with laundry... such
ordinary things gradually but surely loosened the chains of
Lloyd's mother, who bound him.

It might be good to live here with Amina and the others...
Maybe it's time to give up on my mother... Just as I started
thinking that, a letter arrived for Lloyd from the royal
palace.
The sender was Lloyd's mother, Caron.
